A minor accused of posing as a police officer while committing a crime in Meru town has been released on Sh50,000 cash bail.  The 17-year-old was charged in court alongside a mechanic identified as Alex Mwiti alias Kashada.  The duo was in the company of two other suspects who escaped arrest on the night of April 25 at a Go Down in Meru town.  Both appeared before Chief Magistrate Stella Abuya and denied the charges.  Two suspects caught with fake Sh6.4m after anonymous tip to DCI  Minor and accomplice charged with theft while wearing police uniform  Editorial cartoon: Owning a Police Gun  Editorial cartoon: Own a Police Gun The court was told the two resisted arrest by police officers Bashir Hussein and Vincent Kadiga, prompting the officers to fire in the air to scare the suspects.  Mwiti and the minor denied having a government store, namely jungle jacket belonging to National Police Service suspected to have been stolen or unlawfully obtained for use in criminal incidents.  State prosecutor Fridah Mbaya told the court police officers were on patrol when they ambushed the gang.  Take a quick survey and help us improve our website! This comes after DCI boss George Kinoti denied any use of police uniforms and guns in committing crimes within the country.    Residents of Meru county express their opinions on the state of the Kenyan economy  Wakazi wa Meru watoa hisia zao kuhusu miungano mipya ya kisiasa ambayo imeanza kuibuka  Sentiments of Meru residents on installation of Speaker Justin Muturi as Mt. Kenya spokesperson By Joackim Bwana | 30 minutes ago By Nderitu Gichure | 1 hour ago By Fidelis Kabunyi | 1 hour ago By Obare Osinde | 6 hours ago Read The Standard uninterrupted with no advertisements